## v1.4.0 — 2026-04-25

**Amendment**: Added .gitignore hygiene step (Phase 0.5) to prevent worktree directory
re-accumulation after cleanup. Verified in AchaeanFleet session (13 accumulated worktrees).

- Added "When to Use" trigger: worktree directories appearing as untracked in `git status --short`
  of the main workspace
- Added Phase 0.5 "Gitignore Hygiene" between Phase 0 and Phase 1 — gitignore `.worktrees/`,
  `.claude/worktrees/`, `.coverage`, `.coverage.*`, and `.claude/scheduled_tasks.lock` before
  doing any cleanup so these directories do not re-accumulate after the next agent session
- Added Failed Attempts row: skipping gitignore hygiene → worktree directory reappears as
  untracked after next session because the directory itself was never gitignored
- Added AchaeanFleet verification row to Verified On table (commit dcf3d43, verified-ci)
- Bumped tags to include `gitignore`

**Why**: Cleanup without gitignore hygiene only removes the current content — the directories
themselves remain visible to git and will be reported as untracked again after the next batch
of parallel agent runs. Phase 0.5 makes the cleanup durable.

**Verification**: verified-ci — `.gitignore` commit dcf3d43 landed on main of
HomericIntelligence/AchaeanFleet, making `git status --short` clean.

